 :Wizard Book: n. Hal Abelson's, Jerry Sussman's and Julie Sussman's
"Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs" (MIT Press, 1984; ISBN
0-262-01077-1), an excellent computer science text used in introductory
courses at MIT. So called because of the wizard on the jacket. One of the
{bible}s of the LISP/Scheme world. Also, less commonly, known as the {Purple
Book}.